And this is a subject a another wrench friend of mine and I were talking
about a couple of days ago--

In days of yore--the vehicle would start running bad--which was a sigh
of points miss firing, until it eventually stopped on the side of some
oblique road n the middle of no where.
The solution was simple--

Take outa book of matches--use the emery board on the matchbook to clean
up the points--double up on the cover of the matches which would give
you about 0.19 gap, tighten them down and down the road you went--

Today you call a truck--their ain't no way around it--no more quick, on
the side of the road, in field repairs--

But I will say an electronic HEI set up does give you a hot spark, and
with no variation in the angle or dwell for a long period of time with
zero maintenance.

It's a wash--( except when you get the tow bill-)--:>)

A Magneto is the only way to fly--
No radio reception within a 4 block area--but bg voltage--very hot
spark--pretty reliable

Later,

Terry

 
