Perhaps I am the exception to the rule, but I will swear by my Crane
CDI. 
Indeed, if you do want to change at least buy a quality brand name.
Crane has a great rep for ignition systems. As long as they aren't
making them with indentured peasants in Asia now, either that or Mallory
is where I would look. You won't get them for $19.95 and you won't get
10% to 30% better mileage, however, in an otherwise stock T-IV. Neither
can you put in stock points and get home without a tow bill when they
fail, which because of their quality construction might be 10 or 15
years of perfection until nada, and there you is where you is, at the
side of the road, waiting for a tow truck.
